▪ CatSniffer 
Attackers use CatSniffer to passively monitor IoT traffic and gather information on devices, communication protocols, and data exchanges to identify potential targets and vulnerabilities in an IoT network.

This helps network administrators and security professionals monitor and secure IoT environments by providing insights into the data transmitted by various IoT devices.

Listed below are some additional tools to perform IoT hacking: 
▪ KillerBee (https://github.com) 
▪ JTAGULATOR (https://www.grandideastudio.com) 
▪ wiz_exploit (https://github.com) 
▪ PENIOT (https://github.com)
▪ RouterSploit (https://github.com)
